    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Java adopts a catch or throws approach for checked exceptions. That is, if your method can throw a checked exception under certain conditions, you must either handle it by itself or you must declare that it may throw it.</p>\n<h2 id=\"the-throws-clause\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#the-throws-clause\" aria-label=\"the throws clause permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>The <code class=\"language-text\">throws</code> clause</h2>\n<p>To declare the types of exception a method may throw, we use the <code class=\"language-text\">throws</code> clause:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"java\"><pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">static</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> <span class=\"token function\">quotient</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> numerator<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">int</span> denominator<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">throw</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">ArithmeticException</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> numerator <span class=\"token operator\">/</span> denominator<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span> <span class=\"token comment\">// possible division by zero</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>A method may throw multiple exception types:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"java\"><pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">doSomething</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> array<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">throw</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">IOException</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// ....</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>However, note that you don't need to declare unchecked exceptions. Thus, the previous declaration might be simplified as:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"java\"><pre class=\"language-java\"><code class=\"language-java\"><span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">void</span> <span class=\"token function\">doSomething</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">int</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span> array<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">throw</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">IOException</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token comment\">// ....</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Any subtype of the exception type identified in the <code class=\"language-text\">throws</code> clause may be thrown by the method.</p>\n<p>Thus, a method in which can throw <code class=\"language-text\">IOException</code>, may actually throw:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">FileNotFoundException</code></li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">EOFException</code></li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">UnsupportedEncodingException</code></li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"slug":"/exceptions/declaring","title":"Declaring Exceptions Thrown by Methods","course":"Programming Project 2021/22","previous":"/exceptions/throwables","next":"/exceptions/throwing","chapter":5,"section":3,"module":"Exception Handling","banner":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/exceptions/declaring"}},
    "staticQueryHashes": ["800307450"]}